# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Scryfall card + image cache.
# Regenerates itself on first lookup, and is ~43 MB of art that has no business
# in git. NOTE: this means a fresh clone starts with a COLD cache — import the
# decklists before you go live, so the venue Wi-Fi dropping can't blank an
# overlay mid-match.
.cache/

# Saved events and auto-saves. These are the record of a specific tournament —
# real player names, real decklists — not source. They belong on the broadcast
# machine, not in the repo.
events/*.json
autosave/

# Written at runtime for OBS text sources; regenerated on every bracket change.
OBS/*.txt

# Real registration exports — actual player names and their decklists. Keep the
# field out of the repo; the synthetic registration-template.* files next to it
# document the format just as well, with made-up players.
samples/*.csv
samples/*.json
!samples/registration-template.csv
!samples/registration-template.json

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
.vscode/
.idea/

# NOT ignored, on purpose:
#
#   dist/control/   The BUILT control panel. start.bat / start.command run
#                   `npm install --omit=dev` and then launch the server directly
#                   — they never run a build, and the build tools aren't even
#                   installed by --omit=dev. If dist/ is missing from a clone,
#                   the server comes up with no control panel at all.
#                   So: run `npm run build` and COMMIT the result after any
#                   change under control/.